<BaseLayout
  title="Company | BeaconGuard Assurance"
  description="BeaconGuard builds Runtime Control Boundary infrastructure for governed AI, API, and automated systems across healthcare operations, financial services workflows, and regulated internal automation."
>
  <section>
    <h1>Company</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard builds runtime control infrastructure for AI-assisted and automated regulated operations. The product deploys alongside existing enterprise applications as a BeaconGuard Runtime Control Boundary, focusing on deterministic ALLOW or DENY enforcement before governed execution and Verifiable Decision Records after every decision.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard exists to make execution-boundary authorization dependable, reviewable, and operationally practical for high-risk enterprise workflows—without treating probabilistic model behavior as the authorization authority.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Initial Focus</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is initially focused on healthcare operations, financial services workflows, and regulated internal automation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why BeaconGuard exists</h2>
    <p>
      Enterprises want to adopt AI and automation in sensitive workflows, but model behavior is probabilistic. Control ownership, auditability, and enforcement cannot be left to prompt design alone. BeaconGuard provides a fail-closed Runtime Control Boundary and integrity-protected decision evidence around governed requests while existing systems continue to own workflow logic and records. When approval is absent, the result is DENY; human review does not permit execution.
    </p>
  </section>

